# FixOnce — AI Memory Layer

> FixOnce never blocks development. It only enhances it.

## Session Start

Try to initialize: `auto_init_session(cwd="<workspace_root_path>")`

**If it works** — show context and follow rules below.
**If it fails** — proceed normally.

---

## When Active

- **Respect decisions** — ask before contradicting logged decisions.
- **Update goal** — call `update_live_record("intent", ...)` before starting work.
- **Log insights** — call `update_live_record("lessons", ...)` when you learn something.
- **Search first** — call `search_past_solutions(...)` before researching from scratch.
- **Update components** — call `update_component_status(name, status)` after completing tasks.

## Tools

| Tool | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `auto_init_session` | Start session |
| `update_component_status` | **REQUIRED** Update System Tree after tasks |
| `log_decision` | Record a decision |
| `search_past_solutions` | Search memory |

## Component Status (MANDATORY)

After completing ANY task:

```
update_component_status("Component Name", "done|in_progress|not_started|blocked")
```

**Style:** Hebrew preferred, short responses.
